A.9 — Phase A integrated smoke E2E. 2026-05-13.

Run history:
  d9a16040-… (run 1) — agent invoked attach_artifact, got AccessDenied. Caught real bug: worker task role had no s3:PutObject on the artifacts bucket. Fixed by adding BasicsWorkerTaskRoleArtifactsPolicy + redeploy.
  86486ff5-… (run 2) — attach_artifact succeeded, screenshot/goto_url/wait_for_load succeeded. send_email + send_sms both threw "quotaStore missing on WorkerToolContext". Caught real bug: opencode-plugin built per-tool-call WorkerToolContext without injecting quotaStore (A.6/A.7 added the field, but only runner.ts had it wired). Fixed by instantiating PgQuotaStore in opencode-plugin + rebuild + redeploy.
  20f46f85-… (run 3) — attach_artifact succeeded. send_email + send_sms looped with "write CONNECTION_ENDED aws-1-us-east-2.pooler.supabase.com:6543". Caught real bug: PgQuotaStore was sharing the worker's `max:1, idle_timeout:5` postgres connection, which drops under concurrency. Fixed by giving quotaStore its own dedicated pool (`max:2, idle_timeout:60`) + rebuild + redeploy.
  31e06d13-… (run 4) — SUCCESS. attach_artifact + send_email (with attachment) + send_sms all completed, all three output_dispatched events landed in cloud_activity. Browser path (goto_url → wait_for_load → screenshot) also completed. Model stalled processing the 25KB base64 PNG in context (opencode/model-side image-handling latency, not a tool bug). Cancelled to free the pool.

