Bonus (operator-requested screenshot path):
  Run 4's browser path navigated to example.com, waited for load, captured a screenshot (25422 bytes PNG; the screenshot tool persisted it to S3 with its own internal s3Key). Model stalled before issuing the follow-up `attach_artifact(payload=<b64 PNG>)` + `send_email` because echoing a 25KB base64 string back through a tool param is a known opencode/model-side bottleneck. This isn't a tool bug — the screenshot already lives in S3 under the worker's screenshot persistence layer. A follow-up tool that takes a screenshot's s3Key directly (instead of round-tripping the base64 through the model) would close this gap.

Real bugs caught and fixed during A.9 (none would have been caught by unit tests alone):
  1. Missing worker IAM permission s3:PutObject on artifacts bucket.
  2. opencode-plugin per-tool-call context didn't inject quotaStore.
  3. PgQuotaStore shared the worker's aggressively-idle-timed pg connection.

